"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-30-Brazil-s-Rafaela-Silva-eyes-gold-in-Paris-Olympics-1vEdW6jYwxO-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Lucrecia Franco  Copied  No country in the world has won more Olympic medals in Judo than Brazil, with 24. So naturally, Brazilians are eagerly anticipating the sport at this summer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Paris Games. Among the nation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s top contenders is Rafaela Silva, currently ranked fifth in the world in the women's under-57-kilogram category. \\u00a0Lucrecia Franco has her story from Rio de Janeiro.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"